The paper discusses the properties of uncentralisability in systems, which is a topic related to computer security (cs.CR) and distributed computing (cs.DC). The focus on cryptographic primitives and ledger systems also suggests a connection to cryptography (cs.CR) and databases (cs.DB). The discussion of electronic voting systems and blockchain technology suggests a connection to cybersecurity (cs.CY) and machine learning (cs.DL) in terms of analyzing and improving voting mechanisms.
